data.name: Spicy Honey Garlic Chicken Thighs with Roasted Vegetables
data.quickTastyDescription: Tender chicken thighs glazed in a sweet and spicy honey garlic sauce, served with a colorful array of roasted vegetables for a deliciously satisfying meal.
detailedCookingInstructions: In a bowl, mix honey, soy sauce, minced garlic, and Sriracha to create the marinade.
Place the chicken thighs in a baking dish and pour the marinade over them. Let them marinate for 10 minutes while you prepare the vegetables.
On a baking sheet, toss the chopped bell peppers, zucchini, and carrots with olive oil, salt, and pepper.
Arrange the vegetables around the chicken in the baking dish.
Bake in the preheated oven for 20-25 minutes, or until the chicken is cooked through and the vegetables are tender.
Serve hot, drizzling any extra sauce over the chicken and vegetables.
